The paper discusses signal reconstruction from few measurements using the $l_q$-analysis optimization with $0<q\leq 1$, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces a generalized $q$-RIP condition, which is a mathematical concept related to linear algebra and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses compressed data separation, which involves solving optimization problems, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses mutual coherence condition, which is a concept in linear algebra and optimization, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
